synopses.synopsis: A quiz program, this 30 minute show was really more of a chance for comedian Groucho Marx to be very, very funny than anything else. Groucho had a quick and dry wit and he was so unafraid to make a fool of the contestant that he simply never hesitated to do so if given the opportunity. Listening to the show, you often felt bad for the person playing the game, yet, Groucho was SO funny, you wanted him to continue with the humor. Through the years, several famous people appeared on the show as contestants and Groucho would never treat them the same as regular contestants - the stars were off limits to his low-blows. The same could be said about beautiful, single women (or teen girl contestants) and married couples who had large families; they too would be off-limits. Everyone else though had to watch out. The only defeat to Groucho was if the contestant also had a quick wit and was funny; this was rare but happened occasionally. Those people found that Groucho seemed almost stunned with these types of contestants and he generally let them off the hook.
